      • parseCSVTupleSet

        public static ITupleSet parseCSVTupleSet(IApplicationDescriptor appDesc,
                         java.lang.String tablename,
                         java.io.Reader reader)
                                  throws java.io.IOException,
                                         DSMException
        Parse a list of comma-separated value records that are to be inserted into a tuple set with the given descriptor and table name. The first non-comment line is a header and names the columns. The column types are inferred from the 2nd record of values and all subsequent records must be type compatible with the first record. The reader may contain lines that begins with '#' and are comments. Values with embedded commas, must be enclosed in '"'. Leading and trailing whitespace is removed from a value. (double-quotes).
        Parameters:
        appDesc -
        tablename -
        tset -
        reader -
        Returns:
        null if no records in the file, otherwise a tuple set.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - an error parsing the records
        DSMException
